race.comment: Tricky Maiden with plenty of chances. OVERSHADOW (13) closed off fairly on debut when a respectable fifth over 1100m at Canterbury. Kept up to the mark with a 900m tick over trial and gets her chance over this trip. HERMIONE PRANCER (10) her two runs back in stronger company have been okay and will relish Grima's 3kg claim from the wide draw. Adept in all conditions and will be surging late. SAINT ALDWYN (7) resumes. No match for Shangri La Boy on debut when a battling seventh over 1400m at Rosehill in a Super Maiden last October. Given the two trials and gelded over the break. Leading contender. PRINCE CHARGE (6) another from the Waller camp having his first run back. Outclassed when sixth on debut over 1200m at Canterbury last September. Drawn out and stays in the calculations.
